            <h3 style="padding-top: 20px">Stem Cell Transplant</h3>
            <p>
              According to the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society, every four minutes, someone in the United States is
              diagnosed with a blood cancer, and every ten minutes, a patient dies. The only way to cure many of these
              patients is through a stem cell / bone marrow transplant. Nevertheless, when people hear the words "bone
              marrow donation," they often conjure up images of doctors drilling into their spine, removal of bones,
              and
              excruciating pain. The truth is that bone marrow donation is actually a simple, safe, and relatively
              painless process. However, a lack of understanding about this process is a major reason why it is
              difficult for many patients, especially those of South Asian or other minority descent, to find suitable
              donors. Each year, more than 1,000 people die waiting for a bone marrow transplant, according to the
              Institute for Justice.
            </p>
          </div>
